<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 06 at 2:01PM CDT  by NWS Huntsville</headline>
<description>...Clusters of strongs thunderstorm will impact portions of western
Lauderdale, western Colbert and northwestern Franklin Counties
through 245 PM CDT...
At 159 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking several clusters of strong
thunderstorms across the advisory area. The storms were moving
northeastward at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 35 to 45 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Cherokee, Waterloo, Malone, Pogo, Mt Hester, Srygley Church,
Allsboro, Maud, Riverton and Wright.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
